            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": "Large language models (LLMs) with the autoregressive paradigm have gained remarkable performance across various tasks due to their potential reasoning ability Brown et al. (2020); Lewkowycz et al. (2022). The guarantee of such ability in complex tasks heavily relies on chain-ofthought (CoT) Wei et al. (2022) prompting, which provides step-by-step reasoning examples. This approach suggests that the reasoning ability can be elicited through a chain of thoughts, where a thought serves as an intermediate step toward problem solving.",
            "line_with_spans": [
                {
                    "category_type": "text_span",
                    "poly": [
                        445,
                        2047.5,
                        2102.5,
                        2047.5,
                        2102.5,
                        2310,
